1
00:00:06,005 --> 00:00:08,238
Why are we meeting at a restaurant?

2
00:00:08,305 --> 00:00:11,038
Well, I'm banning Chinese food.

3
00:00:11,638 --> 00:00:13,871
- Chinese food?
- We're not going to Chinatown.

4
00:00:13,938 --> 00:00:18,138
Eat while you can,
we're going local in the US.

5
00:00:18,938 --> 00:00:21,171
ACTOR LEE SEO-JIN
LOVES AMERICA AND CHINESE FOOD

6
00:00:21,238 --> 00:00:22,405
DREAMING OF RETIREMENT IN DALLAS

7
00:00:22,471 --> 00:00:23,538
I don't need to go to Chinatown…

8
00:00:23,605 --> 00:00:25,405
- Really?
- …since we're not going to New York.

9
00:00:25,471 --> 00:00:27,771
- Where are we going?
- That's up to you.

10
00:00:27,838 --> 00:00:29,071
Is it not decided yet?

11
00:00:29,138 --> 00:00:31,105
- That's what we're here to do.
- Oh, really?

12
00:00:31,171 --> 00:00:33,438
- But before we decide, Seo-jin…
- Yes?

13
00:00:33,505 --> 00:00:34,871
…let's order some food.

14
00:00:34,938 --> 00:00:36,771
What do you want to eat?
Netflix is paying.

15
00:00:37,371 --> 00:00:40,571
- I want seafood and pork stir-fry.
- Seafood and pork stir-fry?

16
00:00:40,638 --> 00:00:42,771
I'm sure Netflix can afford that much.

17
00:00:43,705 --> 00:00:45,271
So, let's also order king crab,

18
00:00:46,238 --> 00:00:48,371
braised pine mushrooms and abalone,
and <i>Yangjangpi.</i>

19
00:00:49,071 --> 00:00:50,505
Who is the pine mushroom and abalone for?

20
00:00:50,571 --> 00:00:51,905
HESITATES

21
00:00:51,971 --> 00:00:52,805
It's for me.

22
00:00:52,871 --> 00:00:55,771
- What about liquor?
- What? Liquor?

23
00:00:55,838 --> 00:00:57,971
Is Netflix fine with us going anywhere?

24
00:00:58,038 --> 00:01:01,505
It depends on global Netflix viewers.

25
00:01:01,571 --> 00:01:06,238
If they say, "Oh, shit. I don't like it."

26
00:01:06,305 --> 00:01:10,238
That will be the end of Egg is Coming.

27
00:01:10,305 --> 00:01:11,438
That's not my problem.

28
00:01:12,271 --> 00:01:14,405
I'm not an egg member.

29
00:01:14,471 --> 00:01:15,338
Oh, I see.

30
00:01:15,405 --> 00:01:16,938
NOT A MEMBER,
BUT HAS FACE ID ACCESS TO THE EGG OFFICE

31
00:01:17,005 --> 00:01:19,138
DESTINATION CHOSEN IN A CHINESE RESTAURANT

32
00:01:19,205 --> 00:01:21,771
SPONSORED BY NETFLIX MONEY

33
00:01:42,838 --> 00:01:44,938
Cheers. Thank you very much.

34
00:01:45,005 --> 00:01:47,005
- Especially with the hat.
- Three, two, one.

35
00:01:49,405 --> 00:01:51,171
We can do it like this.

36
00:01:51,238 --> 00:01:52,771
I got chills.

37
00:01:54,438 --> 00:01:55,438
It's so impressive.

38
00:01:56,005 --> 00:01:57,371
Oh, my. This is hard.

39
00:01:58,005 --> 00:02:00,638
Sorry, but if you're sick, go home.

40
00:02:01,471 --> 00:02:03,205
You don't look well.

41
00:02:03,905 --> 00:02:06,505
This place has great vibes.

42
00:02:07,105 --> 00:02:09,205
What's so great exactly?

43
00:02:09,271 --> 00:02:11,338
- It's got a great vibe.
- This guy…

44
00:02:16,205 --> 00:02:18,305
READY OR NOT: TEXAS

45
00:02:22,238 --> 00:02:24,738
Why are you filming already?

46
00:02:24,805 --> 00:02:26,271
Yung-suk, move over.

47
00:02:27,605 --> 00:02:30,405
- Don't they have the same hairstyle?
- You really look alike.

48
00:02:30,471 --> 00:02:31,305
Don't say that.

49
00:02:31,371 --> 00:02:32,305
DISPLEASED

50
00:02:32,371 --> 00:02:34,171
The camera's facing this way.

51
00:02:34,238 --> 00:02:36,905
- I know. I'm filming you.
- Oh, I see.

52
00:02:37,538 --> 00:02:38,938
It's a good camera.

53
00:02:39,438 --> 00:02:40,838
We look pretty good.

54
00:02:40,905 --> 00:02:42,338
It's thanks to our big budget.

55
00:02:42,905 --> 00:02:45,771
This is the only big-budget show
filmed on a phone.

56
00:02:45,838 --> 00:02:47,738
THE SMALL PRODUCT OF A BIG BUDGET

57
00:02:47,805 --> 00:02:49,638
Where is the best place to retire?

58
00:02:49,705 --> 00:02:51,605
- Sorry?
- Where in the US?

59
00:02:51,671 --> 00:02:53,138
- Where do I want to retire?
- Yes.

60
00:02:53,705 --> 00:02:55,971
It has to be my hometown, Dallas.

61
00:02:56,805 --> 00:02:57,905
That's my hometown.

62
00:02:57,971 --> 00:02:59,271
It's not New York?

63
00:02:59,338 --> 00:03:00,738
No, it's Dallas.

64
00:03:00,805 --> 00:03:02,038
DALLAS IS JUST THE HOMETOWN OF HIS HEART

65
00:03:02,938 --> 00:03:06,105
NO. 2 IN POPULATION IN THE US

66
00:03:06,171 --> 00:03:09,405
NO. 2 LARGEST ECONOMY IN THE US

67
00:03:09,471 --> 00:03:12,771
SEO-JIN'S NO. 1 CHOICE FOR RETIREMENT

68
00:03:18,438 --> 00:03:22,705
WEARING THE TRADITIONAL BOOTS

69
00:03:23,371 --> 00:03:28,505
THE LAND OF COWBOYS IS
ON THE FAST TRACK TO THE FUTURE

70
00:03:28,571 --> 00:03:34,105
A PLACE WHERE EVERYTHING IS TEXAS-SIZED

71
00:03:34,938 --> 00:03:37,371
EVEN THE FOOD PORTIONS ARE GENEROUS

72
00:03:37,438 --> 00:03:40,605
STEAMING SMOKED TEXAS BARBECUE

73
00:03:41,271 --> 00:03:45,005
TEXAS-STYLE MEXICAN FOOD, TEX-MEX

74
00:03:46,871 --> 00:03:50,071
LET'S GET DRAWN IN BY TEXAS

75
00:03:51,605 --> 00:03:53,671
Let's drop by a CVS near our lodgings.

76
00:03:53,738 --> 00:03:55,405
- What's CVS?
- It's a pharmacy.

77
00:03:56,038 --> 00:03:57,538
Why? Do you feel sick?

78
00:03:57,605 --> 00:04:01,471
We should stock up just in case.

79
00:04:01,538 --> 00:04:02,905
CVS PHARMACY
BIGGEST US PHARMACY CHAIN

80
00:04:02,971 --> 00:04:04,371
He's a seasoned traveler.

81
00:04:04,438 --> 00:04:07,071
We need to get multivitamins.

82
00:04:07,138 --> 00:04:11,538
- We also need toothpaste.
- You truly are a wise old man.

83
00:04:11,605 --> 00:04:13,705
He says we need to drop by a CVS first.

84
00:04:13,771 --> 00:04:15,771
OFF WE GO TO FIND LOCAL HEALTH PRODUCTS

85
00:04:15,838 --> 00:04:19,038
- Can you explain before we begin?
- What?

86
00:04:19,105 --> 00:04:21,404
Why did we choose Dallas over New York?

87
00:04:21,471 --> 00:04:23,271
What makes Dallas appealing?

88
00:04:23,338 --> 00:04:26,838
Texas is the hottest place
in the US right now.

89
00:04:26,904 --> 00:04:31,505
According to the news,
even Elon Musk has moved to Texas.

90
00:04:31,571 --> 00:04:35,338
First, there's no income tax.

91
00:04:35,405 --> 00:04:39,038
But they're still the richest state.

92
00:04:39,105 --> 00:04:40,905
Why is this the richest state?

93
00:04:40,971 --> 00:04:42,705
It's filled with conglomerates.

94
00:04:42,771 --> 00:04:45,638
So, it's funded by those taxes.

95
00:04:45,705 --> 00:04:48,138
- It also has oil fields.
- So, it's rich.

96
00:04:48,205 --> 00:04:50,971
- It also produces oil, right?
- It's the leading state.

97
00:04:51,905 --> 00:04:54,671
It's home to all the oil companies.

98
00:04:54,738 --> 00:04:56,805
And on top of that,

99
00:04:56,871 --> 00:05:01,005
the largest Tesla factory
in the US is located in Austin.

100
00:05:01,071 --> 00:05:02,738
COMPANIES LIKE TESLA AND SAMSUNG
ARE FLOCKING TO TEXAS

101
00:05:02,805 --> 00:05:04,738
<i>- Samsung is one of them.</i>
<i>- It is.</i>

102
00:05:04,805 --> 00:05:07,938
The first thing to come out
of Dallas is 7-Eleven.

103
00:05:08,005 --> 00:05:10,371
- It's an American company?
- It started in Dallas.

104
00:05:10,438 --> 00:05:13,771
- There's one right there.
- There it is.

105
00:05:13,838 --> 00:05:15,405
7-ELEVEN
FOUNDED BY DALLAS' SOUTHLAND ICE COMPANY

106
00:05:15,471 --> 00:05:16,538
Oh, I see it.

107
00:05:17,338 --> 00:05:22,971
As Seo-jin suggested,
a trip should begin at the pharmacy.

108
00:05:23,038 --> 00:05:24,571
Don't bring supplies from Seoul.

109
00:05:24,638 --> 00:05:27,105
But if you do, buy them from AG Health.

110
00:05:28,038 --> 00:05:29,905
Bring only AG Health products.

111
00:05:29,971 --> 00:05:32,238
He suddenly realized
he was the face of the ad.

112
00:05:33,171 --> 00:05:35,471
AS HE GETS OFF…

113
00:05:37,538 --> 00:05:38,871
I forgot my bag.

114
00:05:38,938 --> 00:05:40,571
- Where?
- At the airport.

115
00:05:41,205 --> 00:05:42,038
What the fuck?

116
00:05:42,105 --> 00:05:43,971
A FITTINGLY SERIOUS PHRASE

117
00:05:44,038 --> 00:05:45,771
There was nothing on the seats.

118
00:05:45,838 --> 00:05:47,471
I hung it on the back.

119
00:05:48,571 --> 00:05:49,438
This is bad.

120
00:05:50,005 --> 00:05:51,171
Let's go.

121
00:05:51,238 --> 00:05:52,771
BEFORE LEAVING THE AIRPORT

122
00:05:52,838 --> 00:05:57,405
PERFECTLY CAMOUFLAGED BAG WAS LEFT BEHIND

123
00:05:57,471 --> 00:05:59,371
SEAT SCAN

124
00:05:59,438 --> 00:06:00,371
SCAN OVER?

125
00:06:00,438 --> 00:06:02,571
Isn't that ours? Don't we need to take it?

126
00:06:02,638 --> 00:06:04,805
- It's mine.
- Are you going to leave it?

127
00:06:04,871 --> 00:06:05,971
HE WAS BUSY TAKING CARE OF OTHERS

128
00:06:09,171 --> 00:06:10,471
- This is bad.
- Wait.

129
00:06:10,538 --> 00:06:12,071
- We need to go back.
- Hang on.

130
00:06:12,138 --> 00:06:13,505
- Hold on.
- Wait.

131
00:06:14,171 --> 00:06:16,905
Wait, is this for real?

132
00:06:16,971 --> 00:06:17,871
Did you lose something?

133
00:06:17,938 --> 00:06:20,938
- I left my bag on the chair. This is bad.
- Oh, my.

134
00:06:21,005 --> 00:06:22,038
ASKING THE LOCAL GUIDE FOR HELP

135
00:06:22,105 --> 00:06:23,271
This is a first.

136
00:06:23,838 --> 00:06:25,271
What was in the bag?

137
00:06:25,338 --> 00:06:26,771
- My passport and everything.
- Damn it.

138
00:06:26,838 --> 00:06:27,971
EVERYTHING BUT HIS CELL PHONE

139
00:06:28,038 --> 00:06:29,605
I even left my wallet in it.

140
00:06:29,671 --> 00:06:34,171
- We'll send the nearest staff member over.
- There's staff nearby?

141
00:06:34,238 --> 00:06:36,738
- The production crew left later than us.
- Okay.

142
00:06:36,805 --> 00:06:40,771
- We better tell them to go back.
- Yes, that's what we're going to do.

143
00:06:40,838 --> 00:06:42,371
Shouldn't we go back too?

144
00:06:43,571 --> 00:06:44,738
How far have we driven?

145
00:06:45,438 --> 00:06:47,538
- It's less than an hour away, right?
- Yes, it is.

146
00:06:47,605 --> 00:06:50,171
ANXIOUS

147
00:06:50,238 --> 00:06:53,938
INFORMED THE PRODUCTION CREW
ABOUT THE SITUATION

148
00:06:54,505 --> 00:06:56,038
What does it look like?

149
00:06:56,105 --> 00:06:58,405
- It's a black Bottega Veneta bag.
- Bottega Veneta?

150
00:06:59,238 --> 00:07:01,605
This is really bad.

151
00:07:03,038 --> 00:07:04,471
That's an expensive bag.

152
00:07:08,405 --> 00:07:10,305
What's our estimated arrival time?

153
00:07:10,371 --> 00:07:11,771
It'll probably take 40 minutes.

154
00:07:11,838 --> 00:07:13,305
What does the navigation say?

155
00:07:14,205 --> 00:07:15,638
What does it say, Ye-seul?

156
00:07:15,705 --> 00:07:17,405
It says it'll take 40 minutes.

157
00:07:18,738 --> 00:07:21,171
CURRENT STATUS
THE BAG IS 70 KM AWAY, UNLIKELY TO REUNITE

158
00:07:21,238 --> 00:07:23,005
- What time is it?
- It's 10:10 a.m.

159
00:07:25,405 --> 00:07:28,171
All my stuff is in that bag.

160
00:07:28,238 --> 00:07:29,571
If I lose it…

161
00:07:30,938 --> 00:07:32,638
Then, you'll have nothing.

162
00:07:32,705 --> 00:07:33,971
- What?
- You'll be screwed.

163
00:07:34,638 --> 00:07:35,938
If you lose it…

164
00:07:36,005 --> 00:07:38,471
I'll literally have nothing.

165
00:07:38,538 --> 00:07:42,071
We'll all pitch in some money for you.

166
00:07:42,138 --> 00:07:46,138
No, I'm more worried about having no ID.

167
00:07:47,371 --> 00:07:52,871
NO WORDS OF COMFORT ARE ENOUGH

168
00:07:52,938 --> 00:07:56,638
DOUBLE-CHECKING THE TIME

169
00:07:56,705 --> 00:07:58,205
CURRENT STATUS
26 MINUTES UNTIL ARRIVAL

170
00:07:58,271 --> 00:07:59,338
We've driven too far.

171
00:08:01,238 --> 00:08:05,105
AS THE TIME SLOWLY PASSES

172
00:08:06,171 --> 00:08:07,005
Hello?

173
00:08:08,905 --> 00:08:09,805
ON CALL WITH THE PRODUCTION CREW

174
00:08:09,871 --> 00:08:11,038
Have you arrived?

175
00:08:11,538 --> 00:08:13,038
- Yes.
- We'll get off here.

176
00:08:13,105 --> 00:08:14,138
PRODUCTION CREW ARE BACK AT THE AIRPORT

177
00:08:14,205 --> 00:08:15,105
Thank you.

178
00:08:15,171 --> 00:08:16,938
- I'll be waiting here.
- Okay.

179
00:08:17,605 --> 00:08:19,438
Take a look around inside.

180
00:08:19,505 --> 00:08:21,471
You remember where he was sitting, right?

181
00:08:22,271 --> 00:08:23,238
It was Gate D22.

182
00:08:24,371 --> 00:08:27,005
A WORRIED LOOK

183
00:08:27,071 --> 00:08:30,371
PRODUCTION CREW ARE INSIDE THE AIRPORT

184
00:08:30,438 --> 00:08:31,271
Wasn't it here?

185
00:08:32,805 --> 00:08:36,005
- Did you find it? Is it there?
- What a relief.

186
00:08:36,071 --> 00:08:37,871
Are his belongings safe?

187
00:08:37,938 --> 00:08:40,171
- Do you see it?
- It's here.

188
00:08:40,238 --> 00:08:41,105
BAG SECURED

189
00:08:41,171 --> 00:08:43,605
CHECKING THE BELONGINGS

190
00:08:43,671 --> 00:08:45,105
It's all here.

191
00:08:45,171 --> 00:08:46,071
It's all there?

192
00:08:46,605 --> 00:08:48,505
Are his passport and wallet safe?

193
00:08:48,571 --> 00:08:51,471
- It's all there if they found the bag.
- Okay, hold on to it.

194
00:08:51,538 --> 00:08:52,371
PLAYING IT COOL

195
00:08:52,438 --> 00:08:55,705
- It's all there.
- I thought we'd have to pack up!

196
00:08:56,505 --> 00:08:59,338
It's only day one, for goodness' sake!

197
00:09:00,238 --> 00:09:02,005
A FITTING IDIOM
AT A LOSS FOR WORDS

198
00:09:02,071 --> 00:09:03,005
Just go ahead and retire.

199
00:09:03,071 --> 00:09:04,805
I knew we'd find it.

200
00:09:05,771 --> 00:09:08,005
Are you kidding?
The last half an hour has been…

201
00:09:08,071 --> 00:09:09,938
I wasn't worried.

202
00:09:10,005 --> 00:09:11,005
FOR THE VIEWERS

203
00:09:11,071 --> 00:09:13,438
HERE'S A RECAP
OF THE NAIL-BITING 30 MINUTES

204
00:09:13,505 --> 00:09:16,005
We've done nothing
since landing in Dallas.

205
00:09:17,805 --> 00:09:20,905
It's barely 11 a.m. Why the rush?

206
00:09:20,971 --> 00:09:22,571
- No need to rush.
- You see.

207
00:09:23,371 --> 00:09:26,605
What if we get the bag
and I complain that something's missing?

208
00:09:27,671 --> 00:09:30,238
That would make you the absolute worst.

209
00:09:30,305 --> 00:09:33,238
What if I say, "I swear I had more cash."

210
00:09:33,805 --> 00:09:35,871
- There they are.
- He's got them.

211
00:09:36,438 --> 00:09:37,271
HIS BAG COMES TO GREET HIM

212
00:09:37,338 --> 00:09:38,505
Get out.

213
00:09:38,571 --> 00:09:40,105
I mean…

214
00:09:40,171 --> 00:09:42,105
How many cameras are filming this?

215
00:09:43,171 --> 00:09:45,305
This is unbelievable.

216
00:09:45,371 --> 00:09:46,505
What's wrong with you?

217
00:09:46,571 --> 00:09:48,038
- Here you go.
- Thank you.

218
00:09:48,105 --> 00:09:49,871
- Thanks a lot.
- No worries.

219
00:09:49,938 --> 00:09:52,905
- Nothing seems to be missing.
- I'm sure it's all there.

220
00:09:52,971 --> 00:09:54,438
IMMEDIATELY CHECKS AGAIN

221
00:09:54,505 --> 00:09:55,371
Take a look.

222
00:09:57,405 --> 00:09:58,438
I think something's missing…

223
00:09:58,505 --> 00:10:00,071
JUST KIDDING

224
00:10:00,638 --> 00:10:01,905
Let's get going.

225
00:10:01,971 --> 00:10:04,471
Seo-jin, I'm suddenly craving barbecue.

226
00:10:04,538 --> 00:10:07,371
- What a relief.
- Let's start again from the top.

227
00:10:07,438 --> 00:10:10,205
We are at Dallas International Airport.

228
00:10:10,271 --> 00:10:12,471
This is where our trip begins.

229
00:10:12,538 --> 00:10:13,971
Can I keep my bag in my lap?

230
00:10:15,738 --> 00:10:17,238
Yes, wear it around your neck.

231
00:10:17,905 --> 00:10:20,005
- Should I wear it like this?
- Unbelievable.

232
00:10:20,071 --> 00:10:21,938
SEO-JIN'S TRAVEL TIP
WEAR THE BAG SAFELY AROUND THE NECK

233
00:10:22,005 --> 00:10:26,438
THE DALLAS TRIP FINALLY BEGINS

234
00:10:27,405 --> 00:10:29,538
RUMMAGING

235
00:10:29,605 --> 00:10:30,671
Let's see.

236
00:10:31,238 --> 00:10:33,471
What's in the bag Lee Seo-jin nearly lost?

237
00:10:35,405 --> 00:10:37,171
- His passport.
- The case is made in England.

238
00:10:37,238 --> 00:10:41,071
Yes, I used to have one of these.

239
00:10:41,138 --> 00:10:42,138
It's not that expensive.

240
00:10:42,771 --> 00:10:43,705
What's this?

241
00:10:45,205 --> 00:10:47,005
- Check this out.
- What is it?

242
00:10:47,071 --> 00:10:52,871
- Various cables, such as chargers…
- Look how neat they are.

243
00:10:52,938 --> 00:10:54,405
- Did you see?
- What's this?

244
00:10:54,471 --> 00:10:55,771
It's reading glasses.

245
00:10:57,138 --> 00:10:58,071
READING GLASSES ARE A NECESSITY

246
00:10:58,138 --> 00:10:59,405
Oh, that's what it is.

247
00:11:00,671 --> 00:11:02,805
My poor elderly Seo-jin.

248
00:11:02,871 --> 00:11:05,705
It's thin and light,
so it's easy to carry.

249
00:11:05,771 --> 00:11:06,738
VERY SUAVE

250
00:11:06,805 --> 00:11:08,138
Poor Seo-jin.

251
00:11:08,205 --> 00:11:10,538
EMBARRASSED

252
00:11:10,605 --> 00:11:11,605
What's this?

253
